The '''LM-432''' "'''Muckraker'''" '''crab droid''', commonly referred to as the '''crab droid''' or simply "'''Muckraker'''," was a six-[[Limb|legged]] [[droid]] [[walker]] of various sizes manufactured by the [[Techno Union]].<ref name="Ultimate Star Wars" /> There were other models of this droid that had four [[Limb|legs]]. They were used by the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems]] during the [[Clone Wars]].<ref name="RotS" />

==Description==
[[File:CodyCrabDroid-TCWs3BR3.png|thumb|left|220px|To defeat a crab droid, an opponent could fire into the droid's back.]]
The LM-432 [[crab]] [[droid]] was a [[Confederacy military|Separatist military]] unit that excelled at navigating [[swamp]]y<ref name="Ultimate Star Wars" /> and muddy environments. They were fearsome opponents who hid in the muck and scooted out to attack.<ref name="Join the Battle" /> Crab droids varied in size; smaller models had four legs, and larger models boasted six legs,<ref name="Ultimate Star Wars" /> but were relatively rare.<ref name="Join the Battle" /> Its [[armor]]ed [[limb]]s provided secure purchase when clambering over uneven terrain, and [[Tooth|teeth]] at the tips of the limbs combined with gripping prongs at the joints allowed the crab droid to scale steep inclines. The LM-432's face was dominated by three glowing [[Color|red]] [[photoreceptor]]s, while communications [[antenna]]e kept the droid in contact with its [[Confederacy of Independent Systems|Separatist]] [[commander]]s. The crab droid had two belly-mounted [[blaster cannon]]s for long-range threats. Its forelegs were strong enough to punch through vehicle armor.<ref name="Ultimate Star Wars" />

One of the crab droid's weaknesses was its blind spots. An intuitive attacker could slip past its claws and strike at its vulnerable central [[processor]].<ref name="Ultimate Star Wars" /> Veteran [[clone trooper]]s avoided crab droids' guns by jumping on top of their heads and firing down at the droids.<ref name="Join the Battle" /> This tactic was used during the [[Battle of Utapau]], where clone troopers effectively combated several crab droids, jumping on top of them and shot them repeatedly in the "head."<ref name="RotS" /> However, many [[Cloning|clones]] were cut down by the crab droids before they got close enough to use this combat tactic. Crab droids were agile, they had combat programming and were equipped with a vacuum pump/sprayer.<ref name="Join the Battle" />

==History==
===Occupation of Rodia===
{{Quote|Oh, look out Jar Jar. A crab droid is heading right for you.''"<br />"''Headed for meesa?''"<br />"''Yes, yousa!|[[C-3PO]] and [[Jar Jar Binks]]|<ref name="Bombad Jedi">{{TCW|Bombad Jedi}}</ref>}}
[[File:CrabDroid-TCWCEJtB.png|thumb|300px|right|LM-432 crab droids were used in the Confederacy occupation of Rodia.]]
During the early years of the Clone Wars, [[Rodian]] [[Galactic Republic|Republic]] [[Senator]], [[Onaconda Farr]], was pushed into a deal with the viceroy of the [[Trade Federation]], [[Nute Gunray]], who was secretly aligned with the Separatists. With the proclaimed purpose of protection, crab droids were part of the separatist droid army forces that briefly occupied the Senatorial Residence on [[Rodia]]. In the midst of the occupation, [[Junior Representative|Representative]] [[Jar Jar Binks|Binks]], Senator [[Padmé Amidala|Amidala]], and her [[protocol droid]], [[C-3PO]] were sent to Rodia to discuss the Republic's aid of the planet, but Amidala was captured by Gunray's droids. Meanwhile, in the [[hangar]], 3PO and Binks were attacked by [[battle droid]]s, alongwith a crab droid, which charged at Binks, firing its blaster cannon. Binks took cover, as 3PO directed him from above, though the crab droid quickly approached Binks and unintentionally flung him onto its back. In attempt to shake the [[gungan]] off, the crab droid lost its balance and fell of the hangar deck into the [[swamp]] below. Binks managed to cling to the edge before being dragged down with the droid.<ref name="Bombad Jedi" />

===Battle of Malastare===
The Confederacy used LM-432 crab droids alongside traditional [[B1-series battle droid|B1 battle droids]], [[B2-series super battle droid|B2 super battle droids]], and [[DSD1 dwarf spider droid|dwarf spider droids]] in the [[Battle of Malastare]]. They were part of a large battalion of Separatist forces in an assault on a Republic base, all of which fell victim to the Republic's test of their prototype [[electro-proton bomb]].<ref name="The Zillo Beast">{{TCW|The Zillo Beast}}</ref>

===Citadel Security===
A number of crab droids were stationed at the [[Citadel Station]] on [[Lola Sayu]], now under Separatist control. A Republic infiltration team&mdash;composed of [[Jedi Master]] [[Obi-Wan Kenobi]], [[Jedi Knight]] [[Anakin Skywalker]], [[Padawan]] [[Ahsoka Tano]], [[Clone Commander]] [[Cody]], [[Clone Captain]] [[Rex]], and several [[clone trooper]]s&mdash;was sent to the [[prison]] to rescue [[Even Piell]] and [[Wilhuff Tarkin]], where they were pursued by crab droids upon their escape.<ref name="The Citadel">{{TCW|The Citadel (episode)}}</ref><ref name=":0">{{TCW|Counterattack}}</ref>

[[File:CitadelRescue-EpisodeGuideThumbnail.jpg|thumb|left|250px|Ahsoka Tano takes down a crab droid.]]
When one half of the team, lead by Kenobi, made their way to the airfield where their escape [[shuttle]] was located, they were ambushed by battle droids, with a crab droid dropping from above to block their way back inside the prison. Meanwhile, the group lead by Skywalker traveled through a fuel line to reach the rendezvous point, where they would escape. Upon exiting the pipe, they were met with more security forces and two crab droids approached from behind terrain. The group evaded the attack to the other side of the pipe as a crab droid pursued them over it.<ref name=":0" />

Realizing their plan had failed, Skywalker threw a [[thermal detonator]] into the open pipe hatch from which they emerged and where a crab droid was now standing right above. The crab droid peered down at the hatch before the detonator ignited the entire fuel line, sending the droid flying and landing right next to the [[Jedi]]. Skywalker and Tano confidently walked over the droid's wreckage as they left the scene. Later on, both groups reunited at the airfield with their shuttle, but the droid guards there were informed of the infiltrators' attempted escape, causing more security to engage them. Two more crab droids arrived on the platform and began advancing toward the group, who were formulating a plan of action. Needing to keep back the droids, [[Advanced Recon Commando]] [[Fives]] covered fellow ARC Trooper [[Echo]] as he threw a charge underneath a crab droid, destroying it.<ref name=":0" />

After fleeing the prison complex, the Jedi and Republic officers again encountered crab droids that crawled along the side of a wall toward them. Cody jumped onto the back of one and shot it several times before it deactivated. Being boxed into the side of a cliff overseeing a river of [[Magma|lava]], the group had to [[Grappling hook|grapple]] down to another ledge, but required that [[R2-D2]]'s [[R2-D2's battle droid squadron|reprogrammed battle droids]] delay their pursuers. They were quickly defeated, with the last one being knocked over and crushed by a crab droid.<ref name=":1">{{TCW|Citadel Rescue}}</ref>

Later, the group was ambushed by crab droids crawling over the cliff's edge, which killed a clone officer and nearly another, but Piell cut off three of its legs before penetrating its photoreceptor. Tano and Piell stayed behind to fight the droids as more emerged over the cliff and began circling Tano. While Tano deflected a crab droid's blaster shots with her [[lightsaber]]s, Piell evaded another's attacks and cut its body in half as he ran underneath it. The last two crab droids were finished off as the Jedi pierced their bodies.<ref name=":1" />

When the group was eventually greeted by the [[Low Altitude Assault Transport|gunship]] meant to extract them, they made a swift escape as over two dozen more crab droids appeared at the landing site. The Jedi managed to deflect the blasts and escape successfully.<ref name=":1" />

===Battle of Utapau===
[[File:Crabdroid_bg.jpg|thumb|right|200px|A [[clone trooper]] destroys a crab [[droid]] during the [[Battle of Utapau]].]]
Just before the end of the Clone Wars, smaller versions of LM-432s were used in the [[Battle of Utapau]] against the Republic's [[212th Attack Battalion]] and some [[Pau'an]] warriors. Amidst the battle, a clone ran up to a crab droid, jumped onto its back, and fired his [[blaster]] until it deactivated; a tactic reminiscent of Cody's maneuver at the Citadel.<ref name="RotS" />

==Behind the scenes==
The design of the crab droid stems from transformed tank droid concepts created by [[Ryan Church]] in the summer of [[2002]]. The finished shape was mostly there in a sketch called "droid soldiers."<ref name="DB-crab droid">{{DB|droid|crabdroid|crab droid}}</ref> In ''[[Star Wars: The Clone Wars]]'', crab droids are depicted with four legs instead of six, which surprised Supervising Director [[Dave Filoni]] when asked about it. In response, Filoni noted there was no intentional reason for that design change but reasoned it was simply a variant model.<ref name="Filoni statement">{{Twitter|username=Readingforknow1|url=status/1814709569790132291|name=Editor|date=2024-07-20|quote=Hey @TeamMetaNerdz ! Think you may have any more of this old Filoni interview you included in an old video? thanks!|archivedate=20240720171219}}</ref>

